			<h1><span class="less"><a href="index.html">SLE 2019</a> keynote:</span><br><i>Software Language Engineering – 42 Frequently Asked Questions</i></h1>
			<h2><a href="../profile/RalfLämmel.html">Ralf Lämmel</a></h2>
<ul><li>URL: <a href="https://conf.researchr.org/home/sle-2019#Keynote">https://conf.researchr.org/home/sle-2019#Keynote</a></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t6d.html"><span class="tagM">T6D: Synergies</span></a><ul><li> The keynote is an explicit cross-cutting positioning exercise (definitions, relations to CC/MDE/PLT, practice, education, “technological space”), i.e., synergy/agenda-setting.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t2a.html"><span class="tagL">T2A: Lifecycle</span></a><ul><li> Multiple FAQ clusters directly address lifecycle questions (what’s the lifecycle of a software language; mission completion; long-term evolution of the field).
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t6b.html"><span class="tagL">T6B: Industrial</span></a><ul><li> A significant slice is about SLE “in practice” (Big Tech needs, career profiles, organizational reality), grounded in an industrial vantage point.
</li></ul></li></ul>
